}</script><section id="services-hero-532"><picture class="cs-bg-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-48-03208128.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-48-b9872232.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-48-1d650bd0.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-48-8832e37b.jpeg" height="775" width="1920" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-card"><div class="cs-heading-group"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Talavera’s Trusted Landscaper Since 2005</span><h1 class="cs-title">Landscaping Services in <span class="cs-color">Talavera &amp; Soledad Canyon</span></h1></div><p class="cs-text">Landscape design, hardscaping, irrigation, and xeriscaping built for the foothill lots, rocky soils, and Organ Mountain views that define the Talavera community.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div></section><section id="services-intro-109"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-right"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-left"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><picture class="cs-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-10-94ee5a13.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-10-566831d1.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-10-b54a8499.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Desert xeriscape design on a Talavera foothill property" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-10-7bdf4133.jpeg" height="477" width="480" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Why Talavera</span><h2 class="cs-title">Designed for Foothill Living</h2><p class="cs-text">Talavera sits northeast of Las Cruces at the mouth of Soledad Canyon. Custom homes here rest on 1 to 5+ acre lots with wide Organ Mountain views. The terrain is steep in places, and natural boulders are part of every property. That calls for a landscape approach built around the land, not against it.</p><p class="cs-text">Brainard's Greenscapes has worked these foothills for 19 years. We know the decomposed granite soil, the monsoon drainage paths, and the native plants that belong at this elevation. Our crew is local, our plant palettes are desert-proven, and we design around the boulders and slopes that make Talavera unique.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div></div></section><section id="areas-services-610"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> What We Do Here</span><h2 class="cs-title">Services Available in Talavera</h2></div><div class="cs-grid"><ul class="cs-card-group"><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscape-design.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscape Design</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Site-specific plans for sloped lots, natural boulder integration, and Organ Mountain view corridors.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscape-design/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscaping &amp; Install</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Grading, planting, and full property installs on large acreage foothill lots with rocky terrain.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-hardscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Hardscaping &amp; Patios</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Retaining walls, flagstone patios, and outdoor living spaces built into hillside terrain.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/hardscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-xeriscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Xeriscaping</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Water-wise designs using native desert plants that blend with the natural foothill landscape.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscaping/xeriscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-irrigation.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Irrigation &amp; Sprinkler</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Drip systems zoned for large lots and smart controllers that handle elevation changes.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/irrigation/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-maintenance.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscape Maintenance</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Seasonal pruning, fire-wise brush clearing, and monsoon drainage checks for foothill properties.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscape-maintenance/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li></ul><aside class="cs-area-info"><h3 class="cs-area-title">One Call, One Crew, All Six Services</h3><p class="cs-area-text">Foothill properties need a team that sees the full picture. Slopes need walls, walls need drainage, and plantings need irrigation. We handle all of it with one crew, one timeline, and one guarantee.</p><ul class="cs-area-bullets"><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Design-build under one roof</li><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Workmanship guarantee</li><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Fire-wise foothill specialists</li></ul></aside></div></div></section><section id="areas-landmarks-620"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Where We Work</span><h2 class="cs-title">Neighborhoods &amp; Landmarks We Serve</h2><p class="cs-text">We serve the entire Talavera and Soledad Canyon area under zip code <strong>88011</strong>. From Soledad Canyon Road to Dripping Springs Road, we know every ridge, arroyo, and access road in this community. The Organ Mountains-Desert Peaks National Monument and Dripping Springs Natural Area are just minutes away.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div><picture class="cs-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-4-759f8034.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-4-2c2dac19.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-4-5fc7c2e5.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Drought-tolerant landscape project in the Talavera community" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-4-4598029a.jpeg" height="480" width="580" loading="lazy"></picture></div><ul class="cs-neighborhoods"><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Talavera Community <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Upscale custom homes on large lots with stunning Organ Mountain views. Natural desert landscaping and boulder features are the standard here.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Soledad Canyon <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Canyon-mouth properties with steep terrain and natural drainage channels. Erosion control and native plantings are essential on every project.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Organ Mountain Estates <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Multi-acre estate lots at the base of the Organs. Retaining walls, view decks, and fire-wise plant selection are common project elements.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Canyon Point <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Hillside homesites with rocky decomposed granite soil and dramatic elevation changes from front yard to back.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Sierra Canyon <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Desert foothill lots with natural rock outcrops. Landscape work here preserves the native terrain while adding usable outdoor space.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Dripping Springs Road Area <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Properties along the road to Dripping Springs Natural Area. Larger acreage with open desert views and wildlife-friendly plant choices.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-why-353" class="cs-why-light"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper">Local Know-How</span><h2 class="cs-title">What Makes Talavera Landscapes Different</h2><p class="cs-intro">Talavera and Soledad Canyon sit at a higher elevation than Las Cruces proper. The soil is rockier, the slopes are steeper, and monsoon runoff moves faster. Every design choice we make here accounts for those conditions.</p></div><div class="cs-gallery" aria-hidden="true"><picture class="cs-picture cs-picture-1"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-7-864b7489.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-7-12046b60.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-7-12046b60.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-7-376a7ee3.jpeg" height="594" width="460" loading="lazy"></picture><picture class="cs-picture cs-picture-2"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-walkways-7-0f6ae96e.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-walkways-7-ca8f6ef5.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-walkways-7-ca8f6ef5.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-walkways-7-9d5cb556.jpeg" height="439" width="330" loading="lazy"></picture></div><ul class="cs-feature-list"><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Rocky, Decomposed Granite Soil</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Talavera soil is mostly decomposed granite and sandstone. We select plants that thrive in fast-draining, low-nutrient ground and amend only where root zones need it.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Steep Slopes &amp; Drainage</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Mountain runoff during monsoons can be heavy. We grade for positive drainage, build retaining walls where needed, and direct water away from foundations through natural channels.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Wildfire Risk &amp; Fire-Wise Design</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Desert brush near homes creates fire danger. We create defensible space with low-fuel plantings, gravel buffers, and strategic clearing around structures.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Natural Boulders &amp; Rock Outcrops</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Many Talavera lots have boulders and rock features that are too large to move. We design around them, turning natural stone into focal points instead of obstacles.</p></li></ul><a class="cs-quote-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a></div></section><section id="testimonials-515" class="cs-reviews-carousel"><picture class="cs-bg-leaves"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-5f48081d.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-edeab06b.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-03e85c27.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-8329654d.jpeg" height="1072" width="1920" loading="lazy"></picture><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Testimonials</span><h2 class="cs-title">Let’s Talk About Your Outdoor Vision</h2></div><div class="cs-controls"><button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-prev" aria-label="Previous reviews" type="button" data-reviews-prev=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M15 18l-6-6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button> <button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-next" aria-label="Next reviews" type="button" data-reviews-next=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M9 6l6 6-6 6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button></div></div><ul class="cs-card-group" data-reviews-track=""><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">David was incredibly knowledgeable and helpful. He patiently answered all of my questions about the plants and trees around my home and provided valuable insights into the issues I was facing. His friendly demeanor and expertise made the experience enjoyable and informative. I highly recommend him</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Alexis Silva</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103948667181155023139/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">We had a great experience with David. We used him for one of our rental properties in Las Cruces and will definitely be using him again for the next one. Everything from start to finish was professional and timely. Highly recommend.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Travis Boyle</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108997149124684397289/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard's Greenscapes recently revamped my backyard with rock landscaping. I couldn't be happier with how the project turned out. From start to finish David's team was professional, punctual, and courteous. They helped me select the the right materials and offered additional design ideas. The quality of work was EXCELLENT. I highly recommend David's team to all homeowners in Las Cruces looking for reliable landscaping company. The picture below is of my backyard 1 year later and there is still no weeds! I can't think Braindard's Greenscapes enough.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Matthew Lee</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112275232644298872770/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">I had a sprinkler emergency and David came out immediately; found an effective solution to get me through until the major repairs could be made; and took care to make sure my house wasn't without water in the meantime. I am so grateful for his kindness and professionalism. He demonstrated considerable expertise and decisive decision making that got me through this emergencies with minimal stress. He is trustworthy and will be the first one I'll call on any future sprinkler needs.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Jennifer Wees-Schkade</span> <span class="cs-role">2 years ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113879630740524577871/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard’s Greenscapes is a top notch business. I have called on them on several occasions to fix issues with my irrigation system and for new projects. David, the owner, is a sincere, honest individual, who cares about his business and his customers. His employees are also kind and always professional. They are punctual and complete the job as promised and clean up after they are done. I am very pleased with David and his company and have recommended him to my neighbor, who is also a widow because I know he is honest and will not take advantage of her. David is a good guy and I recommend that you give him a call and see for yourself.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">George Rodriguez</span> <span class="cs-role">6 years ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113926776793747685994/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-projects-630"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Case Studies</span><h2 class="cs-title">Talavera Project Showcase</h2></div><ul class="cs-project-group"><li class="cs-project"><picture class="cs-project-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-21-30243e03.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-21-f34da7c2.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-21-1eeb665f.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Boulder-integrated xeriscape on a Talavera foothill lot" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-21-f273bf18.jpeg" height="411" width="616" loading="lazy"></picture><h3 class="cs-project-title">Soledad Canyon Boulder Garden</h3><p class="cs-project-text">Native plantings woven around existing rock outcrops with a flagstone patio and drip irrigation.</p></li><li class="cs-project"><picture class="cs-project-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-14-d4c9dafa.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-14-201e8639.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-14-add992b1.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Fire-wise landscape with gravel buffer zones and stone borders in Talavera" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-14-40e69125.jpeg" height="411" width="616" loading="lazy"></picture><h3 class="cs-project-title">Talavera Fire-Wise Makeover</h3><p class="cs-project-text">Defensible space clearing, gravel buffers, and low-fuel native plants on a 3-acre hillside lot.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="faq-506"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> FAQ</span><h2 class="cs-title">Talavera Landscaping FAQ</h2></div><ul class="cs-faq-list"><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">What is fire-wise landscaping, and do Talavera properties need it?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Fire-wise landscaping creates defensible space around your home. We clear dry brush within 30 feet, use gravel or stone buffers next to walls, and plant low-fuel species like Desert Marigold and Red Yucca. Talavera’s foothill location near dry desert brush makes this a smart investment.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How do you landscape around natural boulders?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>We work with the rock, not against it. Large boulders become focal points in the design. We plant around them with native grasses and succulents, add accent lighting, and build pathways that flow naturally between rock features. Moving boulders is usually not needed.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">What are the best native plants for mountain foothill lots?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>At Talavera’s elevation, we rely on Desert Willow, Apache Plume, Mountain Mahogany, Agave, Sotol, and Mexican Feathergrass. These handle rocky decomposed granite soil, cooler nights, and the slightly higher rainfall the foothills receive.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How do you handle monsoon drainage on a hillside property?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>We survey the natural drainage channels first, then grade the landscape to guide water away from your home. Retaining walls, dry creek beds, and permeable hardscape slow the flow and reduce erosion. We never block a natural wash; we work with it.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Can you build outdoor living spaces on sloped terrain?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. We build terraced patios, retaining-wall seating areas, and fire pit spaces on slopes throughout Talavera. The key is proper engineering: compacted base material, drainage behind walls, and footings sized for the grade. Sloped lots often end up with the best views.</p></div></details></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-stats-640"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><div class="cs-heading-col"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Our Coverage Area</span><h2 class="cs-title">Where We Work in Talavera</h2></div><div class="cs-copy-col"><p class="cs-text">On the map below: the Talavera and Soledad Canyon area northeast of Las Cruces, including all foothill neighborhoods along Soledad Canyon Road and Dripping Springs Road.</p><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a></div></div><div class="cs-map" aria-label="Map of Talavera, NM service area"><iframe allowfullscreen="" height="430" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade" src="https://www.google.com/maps?q=Talavera+NM&amp;z=14&amp;output=embed" title="Map of Talavera, NM service area" width="1280"></iframe></div><ul class="cs-stats"><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">50+</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Talavera Projects</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">19+</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Years in the Valley</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">5/5</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Average Rating</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">100%</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Quality Guarantee</span></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-neighbors-660"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Nearby</span><h2 class="cs-title">Neighboring Areas We Serve</h2><p class="cs-text">We also handle landscape projects in nearby Mesilla Valley communities just minutes away.</p></div><ul class="cs-neighbors"><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/las-cruces-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Las Cruces, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/east-mesa-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in East Mesa, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/organ-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Organ, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/dripping-springs-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Dripping Springs, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li></ul></div></section><section id="lets-talk-318"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-tree.svg" height="457" width="427" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-tree"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-1.svg" height="20" width="64" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-1"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-2.svg" height="15" width="56" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-2"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-3.svg" height="15" width="46" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-3"><div class="cs-container"><h2 class="cs-title">Let’s Talk About Your Talavera Landscape</h2><a class="cs-talk-button" href="/contact/">Get a Free Estimate</a></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-grass-top.svg" aria-hidd